1
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:41,000
[The Epoch of Miyu]

2
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:43,960
[Episode 34]

3
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:47,920
Tomorrow at 10 a.m.,

4
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,660
the ribbon-cutting ceremony
will start on time.

5
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:51,870
All departments must be
on standby by 7 a.m.

6
00:01:51,870 --> 00:01:53,000
By 8 a.m., we need to complete

7
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,870
the final on-site confirmation.

8
00:01:56,560 --> 00:01:59,509
I have an online meeting
with New Zealand tomorrow morning.

9
00:01:59,509 --> 00:02:01,310
As for the preparations
before the opening,

10
00:02:01,310 --> 00:02:02,510
I won't participate.

11
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:05,200
Is it the bidding for New Zealand's
Yuntian Group?

12
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,000
Yes.

13
00:02:07,110 --> 00:02:08,000
Don't worry.

14
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,330
I'll handle things at the art exhibition.

15
00:02:10,870 --> 00:02:11,750
I'm here.

16
00:02:12,150 --> 00:02:13,950
Let's both do our best tomorrow.

17
00:02:14,490 --> 00:02:15,020
Bye.

18
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,770
Give a tip, sir.

19
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:48,730
I'll do it.

20
00:02:48,730 --> 00:02:49,400
Let me do it.

21
00:02:53,430 --> 00:02:54,780
Come on, Jizhou.

22
00:02:55,430 --> 00:02:55,960
All right.

23
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:56,820
That's enough.

24
00:03:04,870 --> 00:03:05,330
Come on.

25
00:03:06,560 --> 00:03:09,000
To your magnificent challenge.

26
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:09,980
Cheers.

27
00:03:18,030 --> 00:03:19,690
Actually, I'm quite ashamed.

28
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:21,310
I'm almost 40,

29
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:25,240
and I'm still wavering and struggling
between different identities.

30
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:26,740
You know what, Dad?

31
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:28,250
I really admire you.

32
00:03:28,620 --> 00:03:29,400
When you were young,

33
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,800
you knew what you wanted

34
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,200
and what you wanted to do.

35
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:34,150
Am I a failure?

36
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:38,950
I think it's exactly the opposite.

37
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:41,360
There are two kinds of people.

38
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:42,290
One kind

39
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,560
only takes one path in their whole life.

40
00:03:44,940 --> 00:03:45,740
The other kind

41
00:03:46,040 --> 00:03:47,430
spends their whole life

42
00:03:47,430 --> 00:03:49,560
exploring countless possibilities.

43
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:51,180
From the time

44
00:03:51,430 --> 00:03:52,430
you so firmly

45
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:54,280
refused to inherit my business

46
00:03:54,780 --> 00:03:56,860
and went to study your art instead.

47
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,520
From that moment on,

48
00:03:58,829 --> 00:03:59,770
your destiny

49
00:04:00,120 --> 00:04:02,050
was destined to be an exploration.

50
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,160
An endless exploration.

51
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,710
Don't worry about the process.

52
00:04:06,710 --> 00:04:07,800
Just enjoy it.

53
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:09,560
Okay, thank you, Dad.

54
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:11,870
I hope my art exhibition tomorrow

55
00:04:11,870 --> 00:04:13,560
will be a perfect start to

56
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,090
another journey in my life.

57
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:16,680
But,

58
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:19,680
you held such an important exhibition

59
00:04:19,829 --> 00:04:21,000
here,

60
00:04:22,270 --> 00:04:25,230
and even lost a large sum of money
in Hong Kong.

61
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:26,830
Is a big part of the reason

62
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:28,800
because Miyu is here?

63
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:34,300
No one knows a son better than his father.

64
00:04:35,830 --> 00:04:37,380
But looking at it now,

65
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:39,300
I might have

66
00:04:39,830 --> 00:04:41,159
a formidable opponent.

67
00:04:42,260 --> 00:04:44,280
The essence of humanity is competition.

68
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:45,940
Competition brings joy.

69
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,909
No matter the outcome,

70
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:49,430
just leave no regrets.

71
00:04:50,430 --> 00:04:51,000
Right?

72
00:04:52,710 --> 00:04:53,170
Cheers.

73
00:05:09,220 --> 00:05:19,030
[Gilded Years,
Tan Jizhou's Shanghai Art Exhibition]

74
00:05:27,780 --> 00:05:31,340
[5:00 Good morning]

75
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:06,140
[Gilded Years,
Tan Jizhou's Shanghai Art Exhibition]

76
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:12,760
Don't put these flowers
at the door. They're in the way.

77
00:06:12,760 --> 00:06:13,630
Put them on the side.

78
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:14,750
Okay, Ms. Xu.

79
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:58,960
Has Ms. Xu arrived already?

80
00:07:59,110 --> 00:07:59,600
Yes.

81
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:02,040
Miyu.

82
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:21,420
What happened?

83
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:22,870
Didn't we confirm earlier

84
00:08:22,870 --> 00:08:24,470
that there were no problems?

85
00:08:25,890 --> 00:08:27,220
There were no problems.

86
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,830
But the machine broke down at 3 a.m.

87
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:30,770
I don't know either.

88
00:08:30,770 --> 00:08:32,350
Why didn't you report for repair
when it broke?

89
00:08:32,350 --> 00:08:33,320
Where were the security guards?

90
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:33,960
Ms. Xu,

91
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:36,039
we were all following your arrangements.

92
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:37,600
You didn't check it yourself at night,

93
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,440
and now you blame me.

94
00:08:38,440 --> 00:08:39,030
Enough!

95
00:08:41,510 --> 00:08:43,360
I'm not here to listen to you
shirk your responsibilities.

96
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:44,250
Ms. Lin,

97
00:08:44,510 --> 00:08:47,080
please believe that we will definitely
get the painting back.

98
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:48,840
Get it back? How?

99
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,520
Where should we get it back?

100
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:52,090
There are less than 3 hours left

101
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:53,680
before the opening ribbon-cutting
ceremony.

102
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:55,100
Please give us one more chance.

103
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:56,920
Just admit that you messed it up.

104
00:08:57,110 --> 00:08:58,020
Ms. Xu,

105
00:08:58,150 --> 00:08:59,870
you don't need to make promises to me.

106
00:08:59,870 --> 00:09:01,720
I know you sales people too well.

107
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,290
When trying to get clients,

108
00:09:03,390 --> 00:09:05,180
you flatter like no other.

109
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:07,980
But once you get them,
you can't control the situation.

110
00:09:07,980 --> 00:09:09,990
I really doubt what level

111
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:11,250
your hotel considers

112
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:13,190
our art exhibition to be at.

113
00:09:13,390 --> 00:09:15,940
Are you sincere to us?

114
00:09:17,150 --> 00:09:17,750
I'm sorry.

115
00:09:17,760 --> 00:09:18,980
Say no more.

116
00:09:19,550 --> 00:09:21,890
Due to a hotel security incident,
the exhibition

117
00:09:21,890 --> 00:09:23,620
is facing an indefinite delay.

118
00:09:23,870 --> 00:09:25,840
Ms. Xu, save your words

119
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:28,110
for the police and the media.

120
00:09:28,140 --> 00:09:29,000
Cindy,

121
00:09:29,750 --> 00:09:30,450
I'm sorry.

122
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:31,930
I don't agree to postpone.

123
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:33,560
The reporters are already outside.

124
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,000
If we postpone now,

125
00:09:35,030 --> 00:09:36,530
our reputation will be ruined.

126
00:09:36,530 --> 00:09:38,770
Besides, we still have 3 hours.

127
00:09:39,010 --> 00:09:40,730
Let's find the painting first, okay?

128
00:09:40,730 --> 00:09:43,100
Kevin, to hold the exhibition here,

129
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:46,260
we've already paid two million
in liquidated damages.

130
00:09:46,260 --> 00:09:48,320
Are you going to gamble
with your art career now

131
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:49,750
just for this Ms. Xu?

132
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:58,270
I'm sorry, Cindy is a bit blunt.

133
00:09:58,410 --> 00:09:59,610
I'll persuade her.

134
00:09:59,740 --> 00:10:01,000
I'll leave this to you.

135
00:10:11,150 --> 00:10:11,910
Lu Zhenzhen,

136
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:13,770
tell me the truth.

137
00:10:14,210 --> 00:10:16,340
Does this have anything to do with you?

138
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:18,270
Before you start
throwing accusations around,

139
00:10:18,270 --> 00:10:19,660
can you use your brain for once?

140
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:21,880
We are in the same boat.

141
00:10:21,950 --> 00:10:23,950
What good would doing this do for us?

142
00:10:51,270 --> 00:10:54,240
So satisfying.
I haven't felt this good in a long time.

143
00:10:54,110 --> 00:10:57,710
[Purong Hotel]

144
00:10:54,510 --> 00:10:55,710
This time, we finally

145
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,870
got to vent our anger.

146
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:00,600
But I still think

147
00:11:00,870 --> 00:11:02,960
it's a risky move after all.

148
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:05,120
Nothing ventured, nothing gained.

149
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,600
If we don't play hardball,

150
00:11:06,630 --> 00:11:08,870
Ji won't know what we're capable of.

151
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:14,580
[Purong Hotel]

152
00:11:11,060 --> 00:11:13,120
Is the person you found to handle this

153
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,610
actually reliable?

154
00:11:15,390 --> 00:11:17,510
Don't worry, he's very smart.

155
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:21,080
The surveillance cameras
have been tampered with.

156
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,330
In such a short time,

157
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:24,680
they won't be able to find the painting.

158
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:26,640
When the exhibition is over,

159
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,950
we'll put it back secretly.

160
00:11:28,980 --> 00:11:31,440
Then we'll insist

161
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,880
he failed to keep the painting well.

162
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,660
It's a big misunderstanding.

163
00:11:36,450 --> 00:11:37,960
Even if Ji

164
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,000
has the capability to reach the sky,

165
00:11:40,890 --> 00:11:43,200
he will have to take the blame
and get out.

166
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:47,770
Are you sure they

167
00:11:48,390 --> 00:11:50,990
don't have any loopholes
to exploit this time?

168
00:11:51,870 --> 00:11:52,900
Even if they do,

169
00:11:52,950 --> 00:11:54,920
we still have a backup plan.

170
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,850
Ji is bound to lose this time.

171
00:11:57,570 --> 00:11:59,600
But don't let your guard down.

172
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:01,860
After such a huge mistake,

173
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:04,240
Ji Feng hasn't reacted yet.

174
00:12:04,600 --> 00:12:05,930
I think it's not normal.

175
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,950
I heard he was held up early this morning

176
00:12:07,950 --> 00:12:11,040
by some business with Yuntian Group.

177
00:12:13,860 --> 00:12:16,350
Keep a close eye on Xu Miyu.

178
00:12:16,420 --> 00:12:17,370
Don't worry.

179
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,200
Lu Zhenzhen is watching her.

180
00:12:20,930 --> 00:12:22,770
That Lu Zhenzhen under you

181
00:12:23,240 --> 00:12:25,040
has a lot of tricks up her sleeve.

182
00:12:25,140 --> 00:12:26,430
Don't let her sell us out.

183
00:12:26,430 --> 00:12:28,070
Don't worry.

184
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,930
I know what I'm doing.

185
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:50,200
This time, I want to
rely more on my own efforts.

186
00:12:50,200 --> 00:12:51,840
I don't want to rely on you to help me.

187
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:54,740
I have an online meeting
with New Zealand tomorrow morning.

188
00:12:54,740 --> 00:12:56,440
I won't participate in the preparations

189
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:57,570
before the opening.

190
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:13,150
Miyu, long time no see.

191
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:13,810
Yin Xiang.

192
00:13:14,050 --> 00:13:15,530
-Qingping. Ke.
-Miss Miyu.

193
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:16,720
I need you guys.

194
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:19,150
A painting is missing from
Mr. Tan's exhibition.

195
00:13:19,150 --> 00:13:20,320
I've already checked the hotel's

196
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:21,750
entrance and exit surveillance.

197
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:23,540
I think the painting
should still be in the hotel.

198
00:13:23,540 --> 00:13:25,200
Can you guys help me find it?

199
00:13:25,550 --> 00:13:27,080
Then I'll get the sisters
from other floors

200
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,200
to look for it together.

201
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,030
No, the media is already at the hotel.

202
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:32,080
We absolutely cannot make this public.

203
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,550
As long as it wasn't taken by a guest,

204
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:35,210
there aren't many places
in the hotel to hide a painting.

205
00:13:35,210 --> 00:13:36,810
We'll search the place again

206
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:39,040
and let you know if there's any news.

207
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:40,920
Thank you.

208
00:13:46,230 --> 00:13:47,080
[Tan Jizhou‘s Art Exhibition]

209
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:47,960
I didn't find it here.

210
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,270
[Yin Xiang]

211
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:49,870
I don't have it either.

212
00:13:48,770 --> 00:13:50,030
[Ke Wenxue]

213
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:52,550
What about the electrical room
and the parking lot?

214
00:13:52,550 --> 00:13:53,120
[Xu Miyu]

215
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,200
I've searched everywhere.

216
00:13:53,540 --> 00:13:57,000
[Luo Qingping]

217
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,030
Nothing.

218
00:14:00,090 --> 00:14:00,920
I see.

219
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:02,250
Thanks, everyone.

220
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,480
[Xu Miyu]

221
00:14:15,910 --> 00:14:16,790
Mr. Tan.

222
00:14:17,230 --> 00:14:18,090
Did you find it?

223
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,510
Maybe fate was trying to tell me all along

224
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:28,180
that this painting
just wasn't meant to be shown.

225
00:14:28,180 --> 00:14:28,960
It's fine.

226
00:14:31,740 --> 00:14:33,540
I'm sorry, Mr. Tan.

227
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:36,390
I didn't know
that to hold an exhibition at Purong,

228
00:14:36,390 --> 00:14:37,650
you lost so much money.

229
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:41,810
In the end,
I still failed your expectations.

230
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:43,610
No, I was too greedy.

231
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:46,570
I always want the best result
in everything I do.

232
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,440
It's fine.

233
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:49,670
Fortunately, you are its first audience,

234
00:14:49,670 --> 00:14:50,600
so it's worth it.

235
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,320
Mr. Tan,

236
00:15:01,810 --> 00:15:02,480
this painting, "Years",

237
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:05,010
hasn't been exhibited
anywhere else, right?

238
00:15:06,290 --> 00:15:07,550
Do you have any other works

239
00:15:07,550 --> 00:15:09,960
in Shanghai that haven't been
exhibited yet?

240
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:10,550
Yes.

241
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:12,860
They are all at my friend's place.

242
00:15:14,690 --> 00:15:16,930
You mean

243
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:19,860
that you want to replace this piece
with one of my other paintings

244
00:15:19,860 --> 00:15:21,480
and still proceed
with the unveiling exhibition?

245
00:15:21,480 --> 00:15:23,320
We will keep looking for the painting,

246
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:24,550
but as a backup plan,

247
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:25,910
do you think this works?

248
00:15:27,350 --> 00:15:28,080
No.

249
00:15:28,110 --> 00:15:30,140
That painting deviates from
the theme of "Years".

250
00:15:30,140 --> 00:15:31,070
Absolutely not.

251
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:32,920
My understanding of "Years"

252
00:15:32,940 --> 00:15:34,770
is not just the passage of time.

253
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,640
It also includes everything

254
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:39,670
created by the past—
its changes and reflections.

255
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:40,840
It is, in fact,

256
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:42,350
a very broad, all-encompassing theme.

257
00:15:42,350 --> 00:15:44,820
Every moment that once moved you

258
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:47,270
can be considered your gilded years.

259
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,360
But my friend is not in Shanghai
right now.

260
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,000
We have to pick up the painting ourselves.

261
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,340
And his place is very far away.

262
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:58,170
Right now, we probably

263
00:15:58,200 --> 00:15:59,930
only have about an hour left.

264
00:15:59,950 --> 00:16:01,280
There's simply no time.

265
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:03,420
How will you know if you don't try?

266
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:04,750
Trust me.

267
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:16,740
Xu Miyu went out.

268
00:16:21,850 --> 00:16:22,560
Went out?

269
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:24,840
What is she going to do?

270
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,670
Why do you care what she's doing?

271
00:16:27,670 --> 00:16:29,610
Even if she runs to America,

272
00:16:29,630 --> 00:16:31,560
she still won't find the painting.

273
00:16:32,810 --> 00:16:34,810
Seems they are truly at a dead end.

274
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,290
It's about time.

275
00:16:37,310 --> 00:16:38,520
Let the media in.

276
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:41,510
Time for us to escalate things.

277
00:16:48,020 --> 00:16:49,910
Sir, please drive faster.

278
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:50,720
I'm in a hurry.

279
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:51,200
Okay.

280
00:16:59,870 --> 00:17:02,350
We appreciate everyone's time today.

281
00:17:02,370 --> 00:17:05,230
Let's keep up the momentum
going for the next steps.

282
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:06,690
Sure.

283
00:17:06,720 --> 00:17:07,520
Keep in touch.

284
00:17:07,849 --> 00:17:08,339
Bye.

285
00:17:09,150 --> 00:17:09,920
[Meeting is over]

286
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:18,609
We talked all morning.

287
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,960
We didn't reach any consensus.

288
00:17:20,960 --> 00:17:23,220
These foreigners are really something.

289
00:17:23,589 --> 00:17:26,050
It seems a trip to New Zealand
is inevitable.

290
00:17:31,240 --> 00:17:33,440
Something happened at the exhibition.

291
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:40,520
Hello.

292
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:44,860
["Gilded Years" Art Exhibition Media List]

293
00:17:44,890 --> 00:17:47,230
[Organization: Laiyi Media Co., Ltd.]
[Name: Zhao Xu]

294
00:17:50,580 --> 00:17:51,200
I'm sorry,

295
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:51,960
Mr. Zhao.

296
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:54,470
Your organization is not

297
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:55,910
on my media list.

298
00:17:56,370 --> 00:17:58,770
It might not be convenient
to let you two in.

299
00:17:58,950 --> 00:18:01,130
Wait, did you miss the registration?

300
00:18:02,250 --> 00:18:03,550
I have a media permit.

301
00:18:03,570 --> 00:18:05,300
It has your leader's stamp on it.

302
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:06,310
[Media Filming Permit]

303
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:07,790
Or is it

304
00:18:07,810 --> 00:18:09,530
that Mr. Wei's stamp

305
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:10,620
is no longer valid?

306
00:18:11,930 --> 00:18:13,090
How could that be?

307
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:15,400
In terms of publicity,

308
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,400
please put in a good word
for us, Mr. Zhao.

309
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:18,400
Please follow me.

310
00:18:41,440 --> 00:18:43,030
Then we'll see.

311
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:45,200
Everything is arranged.

312
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,000
Mr. Ji.

313
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:48,520
Mr. Ji.

314
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:51,000
I haven't seen you all morning.

315
00:18:51,290 --> 00:18:53,050
I heard there was a little problem.

316
00:18:53,050 --> 00:18:54,810
Ms. Xu has gone missing.

317
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:55,640
Is it serious?

318
00:18:55,830 --> 00:18:57,370
Thank you for your concern, Mr. Wei.

319
00:18:57,370 --> 00:18:59,610
You even came in person to support us.

320
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:00,970
With you here,
it'd be hard to mess things up.

321
00:19:00,970 --> 00:19:02,540
How can I support you?

322
00:19:02,570 --> 00:19:03,390
I don't know anything about art.

323
00:19:03,390 --> 00:19:04,390
I'm just a layman.

324
00:19:04,440 --> 00:19:05,920
I'm just here to join the fun,

325
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:07,550
to see if there are any problems,

326
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:09,070
so I can lend a hand.

327
00:19:10,820 --> 00:19:11,910
Please come in.

328
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:12,430
Here,

329
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:13,070
please.

330
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:50,520
Mr. Tan,

331
00:19:51,130 --> 00:19:52,200
it's time.

332
00:19:52,220 --> 00:19:53,350
Aren't we starting?

333
00:19:59,450 --> 00:20:01,100
Okay, let's start.

334
00:20:01,160 --> 00:20:01,700
Okay.

335
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:09,310
Three, two, one.

336
00:20:32,020 --> 00:20:35,250
[Gilded Years,
Tan Jizhou's Shanghai Art Exhibition]

337
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:35,410
Please.

338
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:38,960
[Gilded Years,
Tan Jizhou's Shanghai Art Exhibition]

339
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:48,110
The images you're seeing now

340
00:20:48,110 --> 00:20:50,110
are a presentation of old Shanghai.

341
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:52,110
Because our theme is "Years".

342
00:20:52,110 --> 00:20:55,750
So I hope that through this installation,

343
00:20:55,750 --> 00:20:58,000
everyone can feel the passage

344
00:20:58,080 --> 00:20:59,610
and changes of time.

345
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:01,350
You can go inside.

346
00:21:04,550 --> 00:21:07,070
On both sides are my paintings

347
00:21:07,070 --> 00:21:09,030
and some photos of old Shanghai.

348
00:21:13,350 --> 00:21:16,070
And as we keep moving forward,

349
00:21:16,550 --> 00:21:18,510
we arrive at modern Shanghai.

350
00:21:28,160 --> 00:21:29,350
So life is probably like this—

351
00:21:29,350 --> 00:21:30,830
while we are walking,

352
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:32,560
time has already slipped away.

353
00:21:32,720 --> 00:21:33,180
Please,

354
00:21:33,630 --> 00:21:34,160
this way.

355
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:47,640
Come on in, everyone.

356
00:21:49,510 --> 00:21:51,400
In fact, for this art exhibition,

357
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:53,350
we've made some adjustments

358
00:21:53,350 --> 00:21:54,960
to the space as well,

359
00:21:55,160 --> 00:21:56,920
all to better fit our theme.

360
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,400
Our theme is relatively

361
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,720
fluid.

362
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:02,210
It's not meant to feel rigid
or overly fixed.

363
00:22:02,970 --> 00:22:03,780
This way.

364
00:22:11,150 --> 00:22:14,730
[Xu Miyu]

365
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:15,000
Where are you?

366
00:22:21,970 --> 00:22:24,140
Sir, I'll get off here.

367
00:22:53,230 --> 00:22:54,160
The theme of our exhibition this time

368
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:57,460
explores the relationship
between time and self.

369
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:01,920
And this painting, "Gaze",
is the culmination of this theme.

370
00:23:02,360 --> 00:23:05,560
We often feel the passage
of time through our eyes.

371
00:23:05,580 --> 00:23:07,310
There are many eyes in the painting.

372
00:23:07,310 --> 00:23:09,330
They are not only the gaze
of the outside world on us,

373
00:23:09,330 --> 00:23:11,230
but also at different ages,

374
00:23:11,250 --> 00:23:12,580
our self-examination.

375
00:23:12,890 --> 00:23:14,160
At the same time, it also tells the story

376
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,540
of how we

377
00:23:15,570 --> 00:23:17,050
coexist with ourselves

378
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:18,670
at different stages of life.

379
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:20,880
Mr. Tan,

380
00:23:20,900 --> 00:23:22,360
you previously announced

381
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,750
that the exhibition would premiere

382
00:23:23,750 --> 00:23:26,820
your never-before-seen new work "Years",

383
00:23:26,840 --> 00:23:29,720
so why has it suddenly been changed to
"Gaze" instead?

384
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:30,400
Yes.

385
00:23:30,780 --> 00:23:33,820
This is actually a minor adjustment

386
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,740
my team and I made
during the exhibition setup.

387
00:23:37,250 --> 00:23:40,010
We believe that "Years"
is all-encompassing.

388
00:23:40,030 --> 00:23:43,220
Rather than challenging its
indescribable image,

389
00:23:43,250 --> 00:23:45,060
it's better to take a different approach

390
00:23:45,060 --> 00:23:46,400
and use a more inclusive

391
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:50,240
and emotional way
to tell my understanding.

392
00:23:50,750 --> 00:23:51,640
Mr. Tan,

393
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,480
many of us here today

394
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:56,240
came here to see the true face of "Years."

395
00:23:56,270 --> 00:23:58,160
Even if for the sake of effect,

396
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:59,960
you adjusted the main exhibits,

397
00:24:00,160 --> 00:24:02,240
the unveiling of "Years"
is still highly anticipated.

398
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:02,830
Thank you.

399
00:24:02,830 --> 00:24:05,640
Then may I ask why you didn't exhibit it?

400
00:24:06,110 --> 00:24:06,590
Sorry.

401
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:07,590
I think I said it.

402
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:09,480
"Years" is not suitable
for this exhibition.

403
00:24:09,480 --> 00:24:13,080
Is it not suitable for exhibition
or is it unable to be exhibited?

404
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,200
Rumor has it that

405
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:17,920
you actually haven't finished
this painting.

406
00:24:18,740 --> 00:24:19,910
Not finished?

407
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:21,800
That's sheer nonsense.

408
00:24:21,940 --> 00:24:23,770
Then why isn't it being shown?

409
00:24:23,790 --> 00:24:26,450
Or did something happen

410
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:28,750
during the installation process—

411
00:24:28,750 --> 00:24:30,030
was there an incident caused
by improper handling at the hotel?

412
00:24:30,030 --> 00:24:32,960
No way. Did the hotel lose the painting?

413
00:24:59,780 --> 00:25:01,530
Dear journalist friends,

414
00:25:01,550 --> 00:25:03,730
please calm down.

415
00:25:03,750 --> 00:25:04,870
I urge everyone

416
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:07,000
to give our general manager
of Purong Hotel,

417
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:07,720
Mr. Ji,

418
00:25:07,740 --> 00:25:09,210
a little time,

419
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:11,960
and let him explain

420
00:25:11,980 --> 00:25:12,900
the current situation to everyone.

421
00:25:12,900 --> 00:25:13,740
Okay?

422
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:15,070
Mr. Ji, please.

423
00:25:20,830 --> 00:25:22,160
Friends from the media,

424
00:25:22,590 --> 00:25:24,050
Mr. Tan has already stated

425
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:26,070
that the painting cannot be exhibited

426
00:25:26,070 --> 00:25:27,270
due to personal reasons.

427
00:25:27,270 --> 00:25:29,450
And as the general manager of the venue,

428
00:25:29,450 --> 00:25:30,610
I assure everyone

429
00:25:30,640 --> 00:25:32,130
that the hotel did not

430
00:25:32,150 --> 00:25:34,470
mishandle the exhibits.

431
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:37,600
Then bring the painting
out for display now.

432
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:38,960
Now!

433
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:39,510
Yes.

434
00:25:39,510 --> 00:25:40,110
He's right.

435
00:25:40,110 --> 00:25:41,530
Bring it out for us to see.

436
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,230
Let us see it.

437
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:48,650
Since you're looking forward to this work,

438
00:25:48,650 --> 00:25:49,850
we have no reason

439
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:51,550
to let you down.

440
00:25:52,530 --> 00:25:54,730
Mr. Tan, you have no objections, right?

441
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:55,880
I...

442
00:26:27,730 --> 00:26:29,170
This interlude

443
00:26:29,270 --> 00:26:31,440
is also a special opening

444
00:26:31,460 --> 00:26:32,670
of this exhibition.

445
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:33,720
Time passes

446
00:26:33,720 --> 00:26:34,960
and cannot be retrieved.

447
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:37,030
But as long as we keep passion
in our hearts,

448
00:26:37,030 --> 00:26:39,190
what is lost will eventually

449
00:26:39,210 --> 00:26:40,860
return to our lives

450
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:43,100
at times we least expect.

451
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:18,630
[Half an hour ago]

452
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:41,780
Are you looking for the painting?

453
00:27:49,380 --> 00:27:51,240
Before being arranged
in the exhibition hall,

454
00:27:51,240 --> 00:27:53,340
all exhibits are kept in the storage room.

455
00:27:53,340 --> 00:27:54,880
The three cameras
inside and outside the room

456
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:55,830
have also been checked,

457
00:27:55,830 --> 00:27:56,860
and there are no problems.

458
00:27:56,860 --> 00:27:58,480
The security department
will also arrange personnel

459
00:27:58,480 --> 00:28:00,290
to stand guard
and patrol around the clock.

460
00:28:00,290 --> 00:28:03,050
We guarantee that
wherever the exhibits are, they will be.

461
00:28:03,050 --> 00:28:04,100
Thanks for your hard work,

462
00:28:04,100 --> 00:28:04,820
Ms. Lu.

463
00:28:13,350 --> 00:28:15,640
Are you from the Engineering Department?

464
00:28:15,640 --> 00:28:16,970
What are you doing here?

465
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,090
Nothing.

466
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:20,790
I just came to see

467
00:28:20,810 --> 00:28:22,530
when the exhibits
will enter the exhibition hall.

468
00:28:22,530 --> 00:28:23,990
I'll get back to work then.

469
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:26,400
You two,

470
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:29,060
don't press the paintings.
Stand them upright.

471
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:39,270
Those paintings are all wrapped in cloth.

472
00:28:39,270 --> 00:28:40,650
I can't tell which is which.

473
00:28:40,650 --> 00:28:42,250
How am I supposed to steal it?

474
00:28:42,710 --> 00:28:43,510
Okay.

475
00:28:43,890 --> 00:28:45,480
Let's wait until it's on the wall.

476
00:28:45,480 --> 00:28:46,590
Let's be clear—

477
00:28:46,720 --> 00:28:48,020
we had an agreement.
The money you promised me

478
00:28:48,020 --> 00:28:49,680
can only go up, not down.

479
00:28:49,810 --> 00:28:51,210
No problem. Don't worry.

480
00:28:57,430 --> 00:28:59,030
They really are up to no good.

481
00:28:59,290 --> 00:29:00,950
Should we secure them now?

482
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,070
No rush.

483
00:29:02,520 --> 00:29:03,730
Nothing has happened yet.

484
00:29:03,730 --> 00:29:05,030
Catching them now is useless.

485
00:29:05,030 --> 00:29:06,610
It might just tip them off.

486
00:29:07,350 --> 00:29:08,210
We might as well

487
00:29:08,800 --> 00:29:11,860
play along and let them take the bait,

488
00:29:12,070 --> 00:29:13,310
and we will swoop in.

489
00:29:20,410 --> 00:29:27,040
[Engineering Department]

490
00:29:31,710 --> 00:29:34,100
[Engineering Department]

491
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:47,540
Surprised?

492
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:50,240
Your so-called foolproof plan

493
00:29:50,400 --> 00:29:51,860
has already been cracked.

494
00:29:53,730 --> 00:29:55,470
The reason we didn't expose you right away

495
00:29:54,790 --> 00:30:00,950
[Engineering Department]

496
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:56,790
was just to see

497
00:29:57,310 --> 00:29:59,550
what tricks the mastermind was playing

498
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:01,360
and catch you all at once.

499
00:30:01,590 --> 00:30:02,850
That engineer from
the Engineering Department, Qin Ming,

500
00:30:02,850 --> 00:30:04,850
has already confessed everything.

501
00:30:05,310 --> 00:30:07,230
He said it was you, Director Qian,

502
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:10,250
who instructed him to steal the painting,

503
00:30:10,680 --> 00:30:13,930
and that you also planted your own people
in the security department

504
00:30:13,930 --> 00:30:15,300
to create gaps

505
00:30:15,330 --> 00:30:16,550
and sabotage the cameras.

506
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:17,750
It was all your doing.

507
00:30:20,110 --> 00:30:20,680
Mr. Ji,

508
00:30:21,370 --> 00:30:24,940
he is obviously making wild accusations
out of desperation.

509
00:30:25,480 --> 00:30:25,920
What?

510
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,340
You believe someone like him?

511
00:30:28,750 --> 00:30:30,610
Can his words be used as evidence?

512
00:30:30,920 --> 00:30:32,080
Then, Director Qian,

513
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:34,410
see if this can be used as evidence.

514
00:30:37,800 --> 00:30:39,770
I've sent everyone away.

515
00:30:40,370 --> 00:30:42,550
Go get the painting out right now.

516
00:30:43,010 --> 00:30:44,120
After it's done,

517
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:46,700
you'll definitely get your reward.

518
00:30:48,540 --> 00:30:50,500
Well... How is this possible?

519
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:53,100
This is the call record Qin Ming kept

520
00:30:53,130 --> 00:30:55,530
to prevent you
from going back on your word.

521
00:30:58,500 --> 00:30:59,410
Mr. Wei,

522
00:30:59,830 --> 00:31:00,550
help me.

523
00:31:03,880 --> 00:31:04,830
Shut up!

524
00:31:05,920 --> 00:31:08,340
Qian Xun, you're so foolish.

525
00:31:09,110 --> 00:31:09,790
How could you do something

526
00:31:09,790 --> 00:31:11,470
so harmful to the hotel?

527
00:31:12,310 --> 00:31:13,310
I'm so disappointed in you.

528
00:31:13,310 --> 00:31:14,380
You brought this upon yourself.

529
00:31:14,380 --> 00:31:15,480
You've completely embarrassed me.

530
00:31:15,480 --> 00:31:16,000
Mr. Wei.

531
00:31:16,030 --> 00:31:16,470
I...

532
00:31:17,030 --> 00:31:18,270
Since both the art thief

533
00:31:18,270 --> 00:31:20,160
and the mastermind have been caught,

534
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:21,230
just handle it as you see fit.

535
00:31:21,230 --> 00:31:21,910
No.

536
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,950
You must deal with this severely.

537
00:31:23,950 --> 00:31:25,130
Don't worry about my pride.

538
00:31:25,130 --> 00:31:27,160
Mr. Wei, how could we not consider you?

539
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,090
We haven't finished speaking yet.

540
00:31:33,860 --> 00:31:34,320
[Tan Jizhou Solo Art Exhibition]

541
00:31:34,340 --> 00:31:34,800
[Major security breach reported
at Purong Hotel during the event]

542
00:31:34,950 --> 00:31:36,760
[Tan Jizhou solo exhibition
held at Purong Hotel]

543
00:31:35,770 --> 00:31:37,400
These false reports

544
00:31:36,790 --> 00:31:38,400
[On-site: Severe security failure
at the venue]

545
00:31:37,430 --> 00:31:40,380
have made Ms. Lin and Mr. Tan very angry.

546
00:31:40,610 --> 00:31:41,630
What's stranger is

547
00:31:41,630 --> 00:31:42,310
that this media outlet

548
00:31:42,310 --> 00:31:44,070
wasn't even on our invitation list.

549
00:31:44,070 --> 00:31:46,800
But their reporter Zhao Xu
appeared at the scene,

550
00:31:46,830 --> 00:31:48,590
kept steering the narrative,

551
00:31:48,590 --> 00:31:50,550
and wouldn't let go of the issue
with Mr. Tan's painting.

552
00:31:50,550 --> 00:31:52,080
Is this also a coincidence?

553
00:31:55,890 --> 00:31:57,540
What does this prove?

554
00:31:58,030 --> 00:31:58,790
It's obviously a

555
00:31:58,790 --> 00:32:00,880
sketchy media outlet fishing
in troubled waters.

556
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:02,160
Shouldn't we just have them take down

557
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,550
the false press release?

558
00:32:03,550 --> 00:32:04,510
But coincidentally,

559
00:32:04,510 --> 00:32:07,030
the time they published
the article was 10:05.

560
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:08,750
Including the ribbon-cutting ceremony,

561
00:32:08,750 --> 00:32:10,310
the exhibition hall didn't officially open

562
00:32:10,310 --> 00:32:11,830
until after 10:10 AM.

563
00:32:12,710 --> 00:32:13,780
I don't know how this media outlet

564
00:32:13,780 --> 00:32:15,580
could predict the future,

565
00:32:15,610 --> 00:32:18,260
knowing Mr. Tan's
new painting would be a no-show.

566
00:32:18,260 --> 00:32:18,910
Also,

567
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:21,110
why is Mr. Wei's seal

568
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:23,640
on this media permit?

569
00:32:22,960 --> 00:32:25,060
[Media Filming Permit] [Wei Siyuan Seal]

570
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:26,950
Can you explain this?

571
00:32:35,870 --> 00:32:37,220
It really is my seal.

572
00:32:39,530 --> 00:32:41,920
It's my fault
for trusting the wrong people.

573
00:32:41,920 --> 00:32:43,030
In just one day,

574
00:32:43,800 --> 00:32:46,230
two good brothers betrayed me.

575
00:32:47,310 --> 00:32:48,410
It breaks my heart.

576
00:32:51,110 --> 00:32:52,070
My seal has actually been kept

577
00:32:52,070 --> 00:32:54,400
by Mr. Huang from the finance department.

578
00:32:54,750 --> 00:32:57,150
Who would have thought
he'd use it for this.

579
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,810
It's my failure in management.

580
00:33:04,110 --> 00:33:04,640
What?

581
00:33:06,180 --> 00:33:07,380
You don't believe me?

582
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:09,310
If you don't believe me, go check.

583
00:33:09,310 --> 00:33:10,770
Feel free to investigate.

584
00:33:15,350 --> 00:33:16,000
[Where are you?]

585
00:33:16,020 --> 00:33:16,810
[Go back to the hotel now.]

586
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:17,740
[Don't act rashly.]

587
00:33:17,770 --> 00:33:18,640
[Trust me.]

588
00:33:28,980 --> 00:33:29,740
Miyu.

589
00:33:31,230 --> 00:33:31,910
Miyu.

590
00:33:36,210 --> 00:33:37,510
So you knew from the beginning

591
00:33:37,510 --> 00:33:38,500
that the painting wasn't lost,

592
00:33:38,500 --> 00:33:40,500
but you didn't tell me a word, right?

593
00:33:40,570 --> 00:33:42,430
I really didn't mean to lie to you.

594
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:43,990
It was them.

595
00:33:44,010 --> 00:33:46,230
They were determined to
ruin this exhibition.

596
00:33:46,230 --> 00:33:47,550
If we didn't play along

597
00:33:47,550 --> 00:33:48,590
to dispel their doubts

598
00:33:48,590 --> 00:33:49,750
and catch them all at once,

599
00:33:49,750 --> 00:33:51,000
we would only be more passive.

600
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,050
What do you mean?

601
00:33:52,070 --> 00:33:53,750
So watching me act like a clown

602
00:33:53,750 --> 00:33:54,310
running around,

603
00:33:54,310 --> 00:33:56,290
was that also part of your plan?

604
00:33:56,640 --> 00:33:57,310
Ji Feng,

605
00:33:57,830 --> 00:33:58,750
is there not even this basic trust

606
00:33:58,750 --> 00:34:00,310
between the two of us?

607
00:34:01,310 --> 00:34:03,070
Is it so hard to just discuss it with me?

608
00:34:03,070 --> 00:34:04,490
If I had discussed it with you,

609
00:34:04,490 --> 00:34:06,290
would you have agreed to my plan?

610
00:34:13,199 --> 00:34:14,340
I know you too well.

611
00:34:15,130 --> 00:34:16,440
You wouldn't have agreed.

612
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,130
Yes.

613
00:34:17,400 --> 00:34:19,800
I would never risk our clients' interests.

614
00:34:20,540 --> 00:34:21,320
I suddenly realized

615
00:34:21,320 --> 00:34:22,850
that I don't know you at all.

616
00:34:23,110 --> 00:34:24,230
I used to think

617
00:34:24,230 --> 00:34:25,510
you just looked unreasonable,

618
00:34:25,510 --> 00:34:27,940
but I didn't expect you
to be truly cold-blooded.

619
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:29,190
You are the general manager of the hotel.

620
00:34:29,190 --> 00:34:30,650
You have your big picture.

621
00:34:30,670 --> 00:34:31,800
But do Mr. Tan and I

622
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:35,110
-deserve to be pawns in your game?
-I never thought about it...

623
00:34:35,110 --> 00:34:36,880
I really never thought about
ruining that art exhibition.

624
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:38,730
Did you ever consider my feelings?

625
00:34:38,730 --> 00:34:40,989
Have you considered Mr. Tan's position?

626
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:42,190
Because of his trust in the hotel

627
00:34:42,190 --> 00:34:43,070
and in us,

628
00:34:43,070 --> 00:34:44,880
how much pressure
and risk has he taken on?

629
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:46,710
You used his exhibition as a target

630
00:34:46,710 --> 00:34:49,370
-to get rid of your dissidents.
-So you're angry

631
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:51,440
-Did you respect him?
-because I used you,

632
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:52,590
or because you did this case

633
00:34:52,590 --> 00:34:53,880
just for Tan Jizhou?

634
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,800
Let's both think about it again.

635
00:35:15,810 --> 00:35:17,470
Let's both calm down for a bit.

636
00:35:18,920 --> 00:35:20,950
♪ I know at the start of every story ♪

637
00:35:21,990 --> 00:35:24,010
♪ They all feel somewhat the same ♪

638
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:28,070
♪ Just never thought I would ♪

639
00:35:28,980 --> 00:35:31,110
♪ Fall for you so deeply ♪

640
00:35:32,810 --> 00:35:35,210
♪ Why did I have to lose myself? ♪

641
00:35:35,780 --> 00:35:37,890
♪ In the virtual world ♪

642
00:35:39,270 --> 00:35:44,480
♪ Unfinished dreams hurt the most ♪

643
00:35:46,210 --> 00:35:47,840
♪ Like a moth drawn to the flame ♪

644
00:35:48,610 --> 00:35:51,850
♪ Wandering aimlessly
through the night sky ♪

645
00:35:53,500 --> 00:35:55,010
♪ Until I met you ♪

646
00:35:55,900 --> 00:35:59,100
♪ Like fire that finally took my life ♪

647
00:35:59,630 --> 00:36:01,410
♪ For your dream ♪

648
00:36:01,730 --> 00:36:03,460
♪ I gritted my teeth
and pushed myself forward ♪

649
00:36:04,090 --> 00:36:06,290
♪ Love really hurts ♪

650
00:36:07,520 --> 00:36:12,180
♪ I never thought I could be so brave ♪

651
00:36:14,730 --> 00:36:23,020
♪ In the end, everything came to nothing ♪

652
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:25,150
Mr. Ji, are you looking for me?

653
00:36:25,150 --> 00:36:25,870
Mr. Tan.

654
00:36:26,710 --> 00:36:27,510
Well,

655
00:36:27,510 --> 00:36:29,760
an unexpected accident
occurred during your art exhibition,

656
00:36:29,760 --> 00:36:31,520
which has caused a negative impact on you.

657
00:36:31,520 --> 00:36:32,980
We are very sorry for that.

658
00:36:33,400 --> 00:36:35,190
It's fine. Come on in.

659
00:36:35,210 --> 00:36:36,120
It's okay.

660
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:38,200
I just want to tell you

661
00:36:38,710 --> 00:36:41,130
that the accident
has entered the investigation stage,

662
00:36:41,130 --> 00:36:43,360
and the relevant persons in charge
have been found.

663
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:44,710
As soon as there are any results,

664
00:36:44,710 --> 00:36:46,550
I will update you immediately.

665
00:36:47,070 --> 00:36:47,590
Okay.

666
00:36:53,510 --> 00:36:54,570
Frankly speaking,

667
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:56,110
during this process,

668
00:36:56,550 --> 00:36:58,290
my concealment

669
00:36:58,510 --> 00:36:59,550
has caused unnecessary risks and worries

670
00:36:59,550 --> 00:37:02,070
to you and your team.

671
00:37:02,900 --> 00:37:05,440
I sincerely apologize to you.

672
00:37:07,030 --> 00:37:08,400
Thank you for your honesty, Mr. Ji.

673
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:10,620
I accept your apology.

674
00:37:11,710 --> 00:37:14,360
Okay. I won't disturb your rest then.

675
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:14,920
Okay.

676
00:37:16,370 --> 00:37:17,060
Mr. Ji.

677
00:37:21,590 --> 00:37:23,430
I've heard about

678
00:37:23,510 --> 00:37:25,420
the bet between Purong and Kuanli.

679
00:37:25,420 --> 00:37:27,080
Miyu, at such a critical moment,

680
00:37:27,080 --> 00:37:28,980
is trying her best
to facilitate this cooperation.

681
00:37:28,980 --> 00:37:31,280
Mr. Ji, you must know why.

682
00:37:33,680 --> 00:37:35,050
Mr. Tan, what you want to say is...

683
00:37:35,050 --> 00:37:35,850
Nothing.

684
00:37:36,230 --> 00:37:38,710
I... I just don't want her to be let down.

685
00:37:39,410 --> 00:37:41,370
I don't want any other reasons

686
00:37:41,670 --> 00:37:43,060
to make you misunderstand
her original intention.

687
00:37:43,060 --> 00:37:44,710
To her and your relationship,

688
00:37:44,710 --> 00:37:46,240
I think it would be harmful.

689
00:37:48,260 --> 00:37:50,260
Thank you for the reminder, Mr. Tan.

690
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:51,190
But,

691
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:53,160
the matter between Xu Miyu and me

692
00:37:54,260 --> 00:37:55,660
is none of your business.

693
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:58,880
Okay.

694
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,720
Hello.

695
00:38:15,820 --> 00:38:16,550
Excuse me.

696
00:38:16,550 --> 00:38:18,040
Sorry to take up your time.

697
00:38:18,060 --> 00:38:19,610
I have a few words to say.

698
00:38:20,720 --> 00:38:22,440
First of all, thank you.

699
00:38:22,550 --> 00:38:24,550
I really have so many people to thank

700
00:38:24,630 --> 00:38:27,140
because you've been with me all the way.

701
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:28,760
But due to time constraints,

702
00:38:28,760 --> 00:38:30,960
I can't name all of you today.

703
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:32,260
But please believe me,

704
00:38:32,550 --> 00:38:34,300
you are always in my heart.

705
00:38:34,440 --> 00:38:35,040
Thank you.

706
00:38:45,070 --> 00:38:46,360
This moment tonight

707
00:38:46,360 --> 00:38:47,560
belongs not only to me

708
00:38:47,570 --> 00:38:48,860
and my team,

709
00:38:49,190 --> 00:38:51,550
but also to a special person.

710
00:38:52,190 --> 00:38:53,190
Because she is the one

711
00:38:53,190 --> 00:38:54,800
who created this moment.

712
00:38:55,320 --> 00:38:56,030
So next,

713
00:38:56,030 --> 00:38:58,440
please give your warmest applause.

714
00:38:58,440 --> 00:38:59,480
I would like to invite my friend,

715
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:00,960
Ms. Xu Miyu, to the stage.

716
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:01,560
Thank you.

717
00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:15,880
Excuse me.

718
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:18,920
Ms. Xu is

719
00:39:18,920 --> 00:39:21,110
the venue manager for my exhibition.

720
00:39:21,930 --> 00:39:23,550
It's fair to say that without her support,

721
00:39:23,550 --> 00:39:26,410
there wouldn't be today's
meaningful exhibition.

722
00:39:33,070 --> 00:39:34,070
So,

723
00:39:34,090 --> 00:39:35,460
Miyu, thank you.

724
00:39:35,490 --> 00:39:36,980
Thank you for your meticulous care,

725
00:39:36,980 --> 00:39:39,100
and your full dedication.

726
00:39:39,220 --> 00:39:41,500
I believe it will be hard for me to forget

727
00:39:41,550 --> 00:39:45,080
this exhibition full of
surprises and sincerity.

728
00:39:45,880 --> 00:39:46,960
Inviting you on stage

729
00:39:46,960 --> 00:39:48,790
is not just to thank you.

730
00:39:48,920 --> 00:39:50,800
Actually, I have a small request.

731
00:39:53,000 --> 00:39:56,030
Because this is our first cooperation.

732
00:39:56,940 --> 00:39:59,000
But I don't want it to be the last time.

733
00:39:59,360 --> 00:40:00,480
I hope we can create

734
00:40:00,480 --> 00:40:01,630
more next time

735
00:40:02,030 --> 00:40:03,560
and create more surprises.

736
00:40:03,680 --> 00:40:04,440
Can we?

737
00:40:08,110 --> 00:40:08,760
Yes.

738
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,000
Thank you.
